def randomized_search_CV(algorithm,tuned_parameters,train_x,train_y,iteration,verbose_int,jobs_int=1):
    """
    This function performs randomized search on set of features, perform cross validation and fit the data in the specified model.
    It returns best set of features.
    
    Args:
        algorithm: Model to fit
        tuned_parameters: Set of possible parameters to choose
        train_x: training data (features) 
        train_y: training label
        iteration: number of itearation to choose random set of parameters
        
    Returns:
        set of best parameters
    
    """
    
    score = 'neg_mean_squared_error'

    print("# Tuning hyper-parameters for mean_squared_error" )
    print()
     
    clf = RandomizedSearchCV(algorithm, param_distributions=tuned_parameters, cv=5,n_iter = iteration, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error',verbose=verbose_int,n_jobs=jobs_int)
    clf.fit(train_x,train_y)

    print("Best parameters set found on development set:")
    print()
    print(clf.best_params_)
    print()
    #print("Grid scores on development set:")
    #print()
    means = clf.cv_results_['mean_test_score']
    stds = clf.cv_results_['std_test_score']
    #for mean, std, params in zip(means, stds, clf.cv_results_['params']):
        #print("%0.3f (+/-%0.03f) for %r"% (mean, std * 2, params))
        
    return clf.best_params_
In [7]:
def weekend(row):
    if row.dayofweek == 5 or row.dayofweek == 6:
        return 1
    else:
        return 0
In [8]:
def diff_day_before_and_last_weeks_avg(df,col_name):
    if col_name=='volume_sold':
        df['diff_day_before_and_last_weeks_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['vdm1'] -df['vwm1']/7
    elif col_name=='maximum_price':
        df['diff_day_before_and_last_weeks_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['mpdm1'] -df['mpwm1']/7
    elif col_name=='revenue':
        df['diff_day_before_and_last_weeks_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['rdm1'] -df['rwm1']/7
    elif col_name=='cost':
        df['diff_day_before_and_last_weeks_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['cdm1'] -df['cwm1']/7
    
    return df
In [9]:
def diff_last_two_months_avg(df,col_name):
    if col_name=='volume_sold':
        df['diff_last_two_months_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['vmm1']/28 -df['vmm2']/28
    elif col_name=='maximum_price':
        df['diff_last_two_months_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['mpmm1']/28 -df['mpmm2']/28
    elif col_name=='revenue':
        df['diff_last_two_months_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['rmm1']/28 -df['rmm2']/28
    elif col_name=='cost':
        df['diff_last_two_months_avg_'+str(col_name)]=df['cmm1']/28 -df['cmm2']/28
    
    return df
In [10]:
def price_diff_max_price_in_previous_periods(df):
    
    df['price_diff_max_price_in_last_day_last_week']=df['mpdm1'] -df['mpwm1']/7
    df['price_diff_max_price_in_last_week_1month']=df['mpwm1']/7 -df['mpmm1']/28
    df['price_diff_max_price_in_last_2month']=df['mpmm1']/28 -df['mpmm2']/28
    
    return df
In [11]:
# Based on assumption that we have mean_retail_price (retail_price on next day)
def price_diff_retail_price_with_max_price_in_previous_periods(df):
    
    df['Retail_price_diff_max_price_in_last_day']=df['retail_price'] -df['mpdm1']
    df['Retail_price_diff_max_price_in_last_week']=df['retail_price'] -df['mpwm1']/7
    df['Retail_price_diff_max_price_in_last_1month']=df['retail_price'] -df['mpmm1']/28
    df['Retail_price_diff_max_price_in_last_2month']=df['retail_price'] -df['mpmm2']/28
    df['Retail_price_diff_max_price_in_last_year_13month']=df['retail_price'] -df['mpmm13']/28
    
    return df
In [12]:
def fit_features_scaler(df_train):
    
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    scaler.fit(df_train.drop('volume_sold', axis=1))
        
    return scaler
    
def transform_features(df, scaler):
   
    df_features = df.drop('volume_sold', axis=1)
    df_scaled = pd.DataFrame(scaler.transform(df_features), columns=df_features.columns)
       
    
    return df_scaled
In [13]:
def fit_features_scaler_v2(df_train,columns_to_scale):
    
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    scaler.fit(df_train[columns_to_scale].drop('volume_sold', axis=1))
    
        
    return scaler
    
def transform_features_v2(df, scaler,columns_to_encode,columns_to_scale):
   
    df_scaled = df[columns_to_scale].drop('volume_sold', axis=1)
    
    columns_to_scale=list(set(columns_to_scale)-set(['volume_sold']))
    df_scaled[columns_to_scale] = scaler.transform(df_scaled)
    
    df_encode=pd.get_dummies(df[columns_to_encode])
    
    df_scaled_final=pd.concat((df_scaled,df_encode),axis=1)
    
    return df_scaled_final

In [25]:
data_model=data.dropna()
products=list(data['product_id'].unique())
for i in range(len(list(products))):
    print("______________")
    print(products[i])

    
    data_model_df=data_model[data_model['product_id']==products[i]]
    for j in range(len(products)):
        if i!=j:
            data_model_df[str(products[j])+'_comp1_price']=data[data['product_id']==products[j]]['retail_price']
            data_model_df['Item_comp_price_diff_'+str(products[j])]=data[data['product_id']==products[i]]['retail_price'] - data_model_df[str(products[j])+'_comp1_price']
    
    features_col=list(set(data_model_df.columns.tolist())-set(["product_id","calendar_date","revenue","cost","stock_level","woy",]))
    
    
    df_train=data_model_df[data_model_df["calendar_date"]<="2017-10-31"][features_col]
    df_test=data_model_df[data_model_df["calendar_date"]>"2017-10-31"][features_col]
    df_test=df_test.iloc[0]
    df_test=df_test.to_frame().T
    
   
    # scale features
    #print("scaling features")
    feature_scaler = fit_features_scaler_v2(df_train,columns_to_scale)
    feature_train_scaled = transform_features_v2(df_train, feature_scaler,columns_to_encode,columns_to_scale)
    feature_test_scaled = transform_features_v2(df_test, feature_scaler,columns_to_encode,columns_to_scale)
    
    
    params=randomized_search_CV(LinearRegression(),tuned_parameters,feature_train_scaled,np.log(df_train['volume_sold']+1),10,0,1)
    model = LinearRegression(params)
    model.fit(feature_train_scaled,np.log(df_train['volume_sold']+1))
    
    Prediction=model.predict(feature_test_scaled)    
    
    
    print("__"*50,"\n")
    print('The RMSE of the Linear Regression is',sqrt(mean_squared_error(df_test['volume_sold'],np.exp(Prediction))))
    print("Original: "+str(df_test['volume_sold'].values))
    print("Prediction: "+str(np.exp(Prediction))) 
    print("__"*50,"\n")
   
    print("__"*50,"\n")
    print('The MAE of the Linear Regression is',mean_absolute_error(df_test['volume_sold'],np.exp(Prediction)))
    
    print("__"*50,"\n")

        if i!=j:
            data_model_df[str(products[j])+'_comp1_price']=data[data['product_id']==products[i]]['retail_price']

    features_col=list(set(data_model_df.columns.tolist())-set(["product_id","calendar_date","revenue","cost","stock_level","woy"]))

    df_train=data_model_df[data_model_df["calendar_date"]<="2017-10-31"][features_col]

for i in range(len(list(products))):
    print("______________")
    print("Product: "+str(products[i]))

    
    data_model_df=data_model[data_model['product_id']==products[i]]
    for j in range(len(products)):
        if i!=j:
            data_model_df[str(products[j])+'_comp1_price']=data[data['product_id']==products[i]]['retail_price']
            data_model_df['Item_comp_price_diff_'+str(products[j])]=data[data['product_id']==products[i]]['retail_price'] - data_model_df[str(products[j])+'_comp1_price']
    features_col=list(set(data_model_df.columns.tolist())-set(["product_id","calendar_date","revenue","cost","stock_level","woy",]))

    df_train=data_model_df[data_model_df["calendar_date"]<="2017-10-31"][features_col]    
    df_test=data_model_df[data_model_df["calendar_date"]>"2017-10-31"][features_col]
    df_test=df_test.iloc[0]
    df_test=df_test.to_frame().T
    
    
    # scale features
    feature_scaler = fit_features_scaler(df_train)
    feature_train_scaled = transform_features(df_train, feature_scaler)
    feature_test_scaled = transform_features(df_test, feature_scaler)

    
    params=randomized_search_CV(SVR(),tuned_parameters,feature_train_scaled,np.log(df_train['volume_sold']+1),10,0,1)
    
    model = SVR()
    model.set_params(**params)
    model.fit(feature_train_scaled,np.log(df_train['volume_sold']+1))
    
    
    
    Prediction=model.predict(feature_test_scaled) 
    
    print("Original: "+str(df_test['volume_sold'].values))
    print("Prediction: "+str(np.exp(Prediction))) 
    
    
    print("__"*50,"\n")
    print('The RMSE of the Support Vectors Regression is',sqrt(mean_squared_error(df_test['volume_sold'],np.exp(Prediction))))
    print("__"*50,"\n")
    
    print('The MSE of the Support Vectors is',mean_squared_error(df_test['volume_sold'],np.exp(Prediction)))
   
    print("__"*50,"\n")
    print('The MAE of the Support Vectors is',mean_absolute_error(df_test['volume_sold'],np.exp(Prediction)))

    
    print("__"*50,"\n")
